revision.text:
{{Intricate template}}
== General usage ==
This template is used to categorize people of a given occupation by their nationality and century on category pages. It will produce the correct links and categories for the specific country and century referred to in the category page's title.

To include this template on a page, use the following code:

<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>{{Occupation by nationality and century category header|Occupation=FOO|JobPortal=FOO}}</syntaxhighlight>

== General example ==
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext" inline>{{Occupation by nationality and century category header|Occupation=writers|JobPortal=literature}}</syntaxhighlight>

== Notes ==
This template should only be used on category pages. Make sure the title of the category page includes the demonym and century so that the template can correctly infer these values. Right now, the category isn't smart enough to handle some redirected categories. In those cases, wrapping the template with <nowiki>{{suppress categories| TEMPLATE}}</nowiki> is one temporary workaround.

== See also ==
{{Template:Occupation by nationality and century category header/seealso}}

=== Sub-templates ===
* {{tl|Occupation by nationality and century category header/outercore}}
* {{tl|Occupation by nationality and century category header/portal}}
* {{tl|Occupation by nationality and century category header/era}}
* {{tl|Occupation by nationality and century category header/nationality}}
* {{tl|Occupation by nationality and century category header/nationality/core}}
* {{tl|Occupation by nationality and century category header/nationality/parentnationality}}
* {{tl|Occupation by nationality and century category header/continental}}

==TemplateData==
{{TemplateData header}}
<templatedata>
    {
	"params": {
		"JobPortal": {
			"aliases": [
				"portal",
				"Portal",
				"jobportal"
			],
			"example": "Literature",
			"type": "string"
		},
		"Occupation": {
			"aliases": [
				"job",
				"occupation"
			],
			"example": "writers",
			"type": "string",
			"required": true
		},
		"Parentnationality": {
			"aliases": [
				"Parent nationality",
				"ParentNationality",
				"Parentnation",
				"parentnationality"
			],
			"description": "Only required if you have a parent nationality category. Typical use is internal",
			"type": "content"
		},
		"ParentOccupation": {
			"description": "Is for a fully nestable parent occupation",
			"type": "content",
			"aliases": [
				"parentoccupation",
				"ParentOcc",
				"parentocc"
			]
		},
		"SiblingOccupation": {
			"aliases": [
				"Siblingoccupation",
				"siblingoccupation",
				"sibling occupation",
				"sibling"
			],
			"description": "See also for a related, but non-nested category"
		},
		"diagnose": {
			"aliases": [
				"diagnosis",
				"Diagnosis",
				"Diagnose"
			]
		},
		"Title century": {},
		"Title demonym": {
			"aliases": [
				"Title_demonym",
				"title demonym",
				"Titledemonym",
				"titledemonym",
				"demonym"
			],
			"type": "content"
		},
		"nondiffdenom_noun": {}
	},
	"format": "inline"
}
    </templatedata>

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other||
<!-- Categories below this line -->

[[Category:Occupation category header templates| ]]
}}</includeonly>

